    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">
                <head type="title"><hi rend="caps">LINES WRITTEN AT THE LAKES IN <placeName corresp="#CUMBERLAND">CUMBERLAND</placeName></hi>. <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER"><hi rend="italic">Derwentwater</hi></geogName>.</head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>Sweet <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">D<hi rend="smallcaps">erwent</hi></geogName>! on thy winding shore,</l>
                    <l>Beside thy mountain forests hoar,</l>
                    <l>There would I love to wander still;</l>
                    <l>And drink from out the rippling rill,</l>
                    <l>Which from thy rocky head doth fall,</l>
                    <l>And mingles with the eagle&#x02BC;s call;</l>
                    <l>While from <geogName corresp="#HELVELLYN">Helvellyn</geogName> thunders break,</l>
                    <l>Re&#x2010;echoed from Old <geogName corresp="#DERWENTWATER">Derwent</geogName>&#x02BC;s lake.</l>
                    <l>And where the lightning&#x02BC;s flaming dart,</l>
                    <l>Plays o&#x02BC;er the Poet&#x02BC;s eye, and warms his heart:</l>
                    <l>Though such thy glories Earth, thy proudest whole,</l>
                    <l>Can never satiate the grasping soul!</l>
                </lg>
            </div>
